# Serene-Mind-App Master Operational Playbook (v1.2 ‚Äî Oct 2025)

**Updates:**

* Merged high-level project overview from üåø Serene Mind App
* Added production-ready scripts, testing setup, and PWA config
* AI workflow fully integrated with NotebookLM/Explore
* Unified developer onboarding and operational guidance

---

## üåø Project Overview

**Empowering wellness through self-awareness, reflection, and productivity.**
Serene Mind is a personal wellness suite designed to support users managing depression, anxiety, and PTSD. It combines **task management**, **journaling**, and **mood tracking** into a unified experience.

### Current Version: Vite + React Prototype

* Branch: `main` contains the Vite/React prototype
* Tech: Vite, React, TailwindCSS, ShadCN UI
* Live demo: [View Live App (Prototype)](https://serenemindapp.netlify.app/)
* Migration work occurs on separate branch `dev` / `nextjs-migration`

### Upcoming Migration: Next.js + Vercel Production

* Convert frontend from Vite + React ‚Üí Next.js 15 App Router
* Styling: TailwindCSS + ShadCN UI
* Authentication: NextAuth.js
* Database: MongoDB Atlas via Mongoose
* AI: Google Genkit / Gemini API, vector search via LangChain.js
* Deployment: Vercel with PWA support

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ Repository & Branch Setup

| Branch                   | Purpose                         |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------- |
| `main`                   | Production (Next.js)            |
| `dev`                    | Active migration/development    |
| `archive/vite-prototype` | Read-only Vite prototype        |
| `ai-collab`              | AI experiments & subagent tasks |

**Steps:**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/CjDaOne/Serene-Mind-App.git
cd Serene-Mind-App
git checkout -b dev
```

* Create missing branches: `archive/vite-prototype`, `ai-collab`
* Protect `main` branch, enforce PR-only merges
* Configure GitHub Actions for linting, typechecking, testing, and Vercel deploys

